Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications Benjamin Rhodes met with representatives of the Iraqi Christian community at the White House. He updated them on the President's recent discussion with the Iraqi Prime Minister and the progress in the global campaign against ISIL. The delegation shared the challenges faced by the Iraqi Christian community, and Rhodes reiterated the President's commitment to supporting all of Iraq's diverse communities, including Christians, Sabean-Mandaeans, Shabak, Yezidis, and other ethnic and religious minorities. He also expressed deep concern over the threat ISIL poses to these communities and to all Iraqis.